        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 2:28PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 227 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hanging Rock State Park, or near Francisco, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stuart...
Danbury...
Spencer...
Sandy Ridge...
Francisco...
Critz...
and Horse Pasture.
</description>
        <instruction>Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
